R \u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":249,"html":250},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":252,"html":253},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>As Bivona notes, Mommsen in CIL chose to unify this fragment with one recorded by Gualtherus and Fazello (ISic001896, on a piece of an architrave, re-used as a church step, and which read: IMP. M. AVRELIO . ANTONINO . AVG...). However. Torremuzza described that piece separately from this one, which he placed in the courtyard of the Palazzo Senatorio, and there seems no obvious reason to conflate them.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":255,"html":256},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1762 13 no.xxiv \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650789\" target=\"_blank\">7277\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1970 19 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1988 78 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":258,"html":259},"handnote"," \u003Cp>Tall and very narrow letters, fairly crudely carved, with AV in ligature.\u003C/p> Line 1  105  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":261,"html":262},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[264,266,269,271,274,275,278,279],{"html":265},"Text encoding: Tuuli Ahlholm, Jonathan Prag",{"id":267,"lang":126,"html":2